awa D'Estain.<br>
<br>
I would like to bring to your attention the recent banning of Mystere, of Brell Serilis, for a particular roleplaying story.  A story which was rather graphic, agreed - but I would also like to draw to your attention  that it was not posted on an official EverQuest board, and was written under legitimate roleplaying style.  It was vile, just as the teir'dal were designed to be.<br>
<br>
Go to www.lumthemad.com for the specifics.<br>
<br>
I do have motives for bringing this up.  I am not merely mentioning this from sheer whim.  I am outraged.  I am a seething sack of venom, actually.  If I had the ability to do so, I would use my virtually nonexistant persuasion skills to whip my rage towards a furious holocaust and into you, my readers.  But I am not a persuasive being.  I merely request that you go to the above mentioned site and look at this for what it is - a hideous attack on the right to CREATIVITY which you as an EverQuest Player, as a god-damned HUMAN, are imbued with and entitled to.  Read it, please, if you can, and tell me what you think.<br>
<br>
You know what I think already.<br>
<br>
And if you care, if you have any interest or belief in the Right to Expression and Creativity, we better damned well do something about this.<br>
<br>
--Rich <p>--The Destain, Humwawa Dosoloth <BR>
